                <h1>Robert Hayden: A Pioneer of African American Poetry</h1>
                <p>Robert Hayden was a prominent African American poet, known for his profound works exploring themes of race, identity, and history. Born in 1913 in Detroit, Michigan, his most celebrated pieces include "Those Winter Sundays" and "Middle Passage." Hayden's unique voice captured the African American experience, influencing generations of poets.</p>
